100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 17, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament discussions amid rising tensions across Europe. In the United States, the Supreme Court upheld the constitutionality of the National Prohibition Act, affirming the federal government's stance on alcohol prohibition. Meanwhile, in Turkey, significant political shifts were underway as Mustafa Kemal Atatrk continued to push for modernization and secular reforms.
